Some EU Members Seeking Aggressive Greek Writedown, Reuters Says

-- B y   J o h n   F r a h e r
-- 
2011-10-20T08:29:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-20/some-eu-members-seeking-aggressive-greek-writedown-reuters-says.html
The Greek debt writedowns pushed by
some European governments may be too large to be accepted
voluntarily by investors and may instead have to be forced on
them, Reuters said, citing unidentified European Union
officials.   Banks will not voluntarily accept a 50 percent haircut,
Reuters said, citing one of the officials.   To contact the reporter on this story:
